&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Golden State is looking for a Director to lead the accounting team for our professional sports franchises and related business entities. This is a pivotal role responsible for ensuring the integrity of the GAAP financial statements while navigating the unique complexities of sports accounting, including league-mandated reporting.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the primary accounting stakeholder for the sports business, you will drive the monthly close, lead NBA league-mandated reporting, and serve as the subject matter expert for technical guidance. We need a hands-on leader who can move seamlessly between high-level process improvement and granular technical memos. In this role, you will not only manage the numbers, but also translate financial results into strategic narratives for non-technical business partners, ensuring that the accounting function acts as a true partner to the operations and executive teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Come share your expertise while joining a growing and exciting sports and entertainment organization that values your initiative, creativity, and dedication.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This is a full-time position based on-site in San Francisco, CA.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct all GL activities, ensuring a “no surprises” month-end close; own the accuracy of the Balance Sheet, Income Statement, and Statement of Cash Flows for the sports entities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the month-end, quarter-end, and year-end close processes, including meticulous account reconciliations and flux analyses to explain variances to prior periods&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee complex revenue streams unique to sports, including multi-year sponsorship deals, broadcasting rights, and ticket sales, ensuring compliance with ASC 606&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the accounting for fixed assets and the leasing portfolio, ensuring rigorous adherence to ASC 842&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Direct the preparation of all NBA League Reporting and ensure compliance with league-mandated accounting guidelines and audits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and author technical accounting memos on complex revenue, customer, and vendor transactions (e.g., media rights, sponsorships, ticketing, concessions, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as the primary point of contact for technical accounting issues, effectively communicating risks and solutions to non-technical business partners and executive leadership&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage the annual external audit process, ensuring all schedules are prepared accurately and delivered on schedule&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and implement process improvements to streamline the close cycle and enhance internal controls&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead quarterly accounting reviews, providing senior leadership with a clear narrative of financial performance and operational trends&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Legal, FP&amp;amp;A, Sales, and Operations to ensure accounting workflows support broader business objectives&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentor, motivate, and manage a team of accounting professionals, fostering a culture of continuous learning and operational excellence&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Clearly define career paths and performance expectations to ensure the team is set-up for long term success&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Other duties as assigned&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Required Experience and Skills&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree, preferably in Accounting, or equivalent work experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Certified Public Accountant (CPA) certification preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;7+ years of progressive accounting experience; 1-2 years of people management experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in US GAAP; familiarity with NBA reporting standards is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&g

